explanation: This solution uses a while loop to repeatedly remove pairs of adjacent characters that are consecutive in the alphabet. It uses a for loop to check each pair of adjacent characters in the string. If a pair is found, it removes the pair from the string and breaks the loop. If no pairs are found, it breaks the while loop. This solution has a high efficiency because it only checks each pair of adjacent characters once, but it has a time complexity of O(n^2) because it uses a for loop inside a while loop.

